## Maintenance

### Re-rendering after edits

Run `./render.sh` to regenerate all SVGs, or `./render.sh <NN>` for a single file. SVGs are under git in this convention; commit them alongside the `.md` source.

### Drift detection after revisions

When `/ddd:revise` classifies a change as `cascading`, the manifest row will list `diagrams-affected: [T<n.n>, ...]`. Run `/ddd:diagrams --resync` to walk the affected list and refresh those diagrams (per-diagram gate). Per `kb/patterns/artifact-impact-matrix.md § Diagrams as a downstream type`.

### Adding new diagrams

If the project matures past a Tier 2/3/4 threshold (e.g. you cross 10 ADRs and now want T4.2 ADR Dependency Graph), simply re-run `/ddd:diagrams`. Existing diagrams are not regenerated; new ones are added.

